main event: A balloon was found in a roadside ditch 12 miles north and 7 miles east of Cedar Falls, Iowa on December 12, 1956, and was later identified as an unidentified balloon.
interesting points: No evidence of special or unusual characteristics was found regarding the balloon,An extensive check revealed that the balloon was not an experimental or training balloon of any type,The remains of the balloon envelope were in shreds 10-15 feet in length,The balloon was suspected to have been launched from a site in California but this was eliminated as a possibility,Previous similar findings were noted but did not contain identifiers or rewards as in past cases.
witness description: Mr. found the balloon in a roadside ditch.
